name: Parks Hall
directions: Near the lobby area of the West side of the building

name: Biomedical Research Tower
directions: First floor next to Brenen's Cafe

name: Boline Apothecary, Limited
directions: Near the corner of High and Beechwold, which is just south of Morse Road.
comment: Place is queer and kid friendly. Kids table in corner, bathroom towards the back, though the apothecary. Just ask.

name: Queen Margaret Union
directions: Third floor, left out of the lift, at the end of the corridor.

name: Madhyamaka Kadampa Meditation Centre
directions: In the main house. From the front door, follow the corridor, through a door, and they're on the right. (2 stalls.)
comment: Bit out of the way so I'm not sure how useful this is for emergencies, but it's there.

name: Togos
directions: Need a key. straight back.
comment: Unisex. Handicap. Need a key.

name: Nubi Yogurt
comment: "Restroom for patrons' use only"

name: Chico Art Center
directions: Part of the Train Station, Up the Stairs
comment: Depending on who is working, they'll want you to just look around the gallery for a few minutes, no cost. Open every day, 10-4.

name: Naked Lounge
comment: Not totally positive on wheelchair accessibility, must be paying customer or with someone that is.

name: Bell Memorial Union
directions: Building actually faces 2nd St towards parking lot, Down the stairs to the basement, turn left.
comment: Three "All Gender Restrooms," Single rooms that lock, next to a common area that students use to study so people coming and going is unnoticed.

name: Strangelove's
directions: Between Walnut & Locust on 11th St.
comment: best gender neutral bathrooms I have seen in a bar... individual toilets with a common sink that links the 4 rooms.

name: Whole Foods
directions: At the front of the store on the right, past the seating area.

name: Starbucks
comment: Have to be a paying customer.

name: 7th Dimension Games
directions: They only have a single stall room.
comment: Available to all customers or potential customers. They sell $1 candy if you don't need an expensive game.

name: Combibos caf√©
directions: Go to the back of the caf√© and turn right, it's the door marked 'Manager'.
comment:
For paying customers, though staff are friendly, so maybe worth asking if you can just use the loo.
RE: accessibility - there is a small step to get into the caf√©, and the bathroom is large, with a large door, but no handrail/emergency cord.

name: Baby Love Bar
directions: Downstairs, turn right and right again
comment: Club; open nights, have to pay entry

name: The Plush Lounge
comment: This is a gay club, i.e. only open at night, and you will need to pay entry.

name: All Souls Unitarian Church
directions: All 3 bathrooms are located by the main entrance. The accessible/gender neutral bathroom is closest to the door, followed my Men's and then Women's.
comment: These bathrooms are safe places.

name: Equality Ohio
directions: Activate the key pad outside and buzz in to Equality Ohio. Tell them you found it on Refugee Restroom, then hit up the 2nd floor.
comment: EO is a statewide LGBT advocacy org. Normally 9-5 Monday through Friday.

name: HALF PRICE BOOK
directions: BOTH BATHROOMS ARE SINGLE USE

name: Geeksboro Coffeehouse Cinema
directions: Main floor in the back on the left. There is a very spacious wheelchair accessible family restroom (sign says "Marvel Family"). There are also "Spider-Man" and "Wonder Woman" labeled bathrooms but they are truely unisex facilities. All are single toilets with a sink.
comment: A purchase is not required. If other customers harass anyone for their gender identity they will be asked to leave. Geeksboro have a zero tolerance policy for that kind of behavior.

name: Walmart
directions: All the way in the back by layaway.

name: Bath and Body Works
directions: It's right inside the front door (parking lot side) to the left.
comment: I don't know if it's locked  or if you have to buy anything so be prepared to buy something but you might not have to

name: Sam's Club Warehouse
directions: The separate "Family" restroom is straight ahead to the left when you walk in, right next to the gendered bathrooms.
comment: Must be Sam's Club member, but you may be able to get a pass to come in without being a member (e.g. a 1-day pass; or to use the pharmacy).

name: Ulrich
directions: In the back, next to the gendered single stall Men's restroom. There are also two gendered single-stall bathrooms.
comment: You have to be a restaurant customer.

name: Verdigris Tea Cafe & Bakery
directions: On the corner of Warren and Sourh 2nd St. Restroom  is in the back on the right by the drink kiosk.
comment: Cool place.

name: Chipotle Grill
directions: Gendered single stall restroom inside the chipotle.

name: A La Mode Cafe and Catering
Park City Mall
directions: In the boscovs wing where the other bathrooms are, are two "family bathrooms" that are for use by anyone.
comment: available for anyone to use

name: Burgermeister
comment: Locking door. Statement of safety.

name: Qdoba
directions: Mailing address is 555 11 St, but entrance is on E St between 10th and 11th, next to the E Street Cinema.
comment:
2 lockable single-person unisex restrooms, with foldaway changing tables.

Officially accessible, but difficult; there is a somewhat elderly folding platform lift to go up a short flight of 4-5 stairs between restaurant main floor and restrooms.

name: The Independent
directions: In the front in a corner
comment: Don't use it unless you're eating there.

name: El Potro
directions: In back
comment: Don't use it unless you're eating there.

name: Starbucks
directions: Over in the corner past the drink pickup counter
comment: Gendered, but nobody really cares which you use especially if there's a line. Not locked unless in use so you don't have to be a customer

name: Harbour Centre
directions: Main floor of SFU single rooms, one down the first left at the main entrance and the other first right and past the elevators from the main entrance.

name: Little Delhi
comment: Restrooms for paying customers.

name: Books-A-Million
directions: In the back of the store, on the right side

name: University Hall, Purdue University
directions: 2nd Floor Unisex Bathroom - in the middle of the hall between the two stairwells
comment: The building is the oldest on campus so it's not wheelchair friendly.  You'll need to climb some stairs to get into the building.

name: Washtenaw Community College
directions: 5 accessible restrooms are available in the Gunder Myran building on WCC's campus. Two are found on the third floor, two on the second floor and one on the ground floor. All are located close to a stairwell and elevators.
comment: These are the only restrooms on campus available to students that are gender-neutral. There exists multiple accessible staff restrooms throughout campus that require a key for access.

name: Loaded Joe's
directions: In a shopping center; only one restroom located in the far back corner of the bar.
comment: Not sure if it is accessible, honestly...it doesn't look accessible at all, though.

name: Spicar's Martial Arts
directions: In the very back. The building is next to Kroger in the shopping center and has a big sign that says "Karate", which is the best way to find it.
comment: Because it is in the back, getting to either of the bathrooms requires walking through the studio which is slightly difficult when in a wheelchair because there is only a narrow space of tile to get back there.

name: Wisey's
directions: Take the stairs in front of you as you walk in the door and it'll be right in front of you.
comment: Not sure if you need a key. I didn't, but the person behind me asked if I had a key. I don't know if you have to be a "paying customer". I bought a smoothie because I wanted one anyway.

name: Shemer Art Center
directions: Within art center, hallway between gallery rooms.

name: Starbucks
directions: If you're facing the counter, it's to the right of the bar and in the back of the building
comment: Staff is very open-minded and trans positive. Bathrooms are around a corner and kind of "hidden", so if you're nervous about people seeing you go in/out you're safe.

name: Walmart
directions: off hwy 11 and taylor rd.
comment: turn left once you enter the doors and head down the hallway past the service desk, it's a family/handicap single use washroom.

name: Del Vecchios
directions:
They are located in the second half of the restaurant.

When you walk in, go to the right, through a set of doors on your left, and immediately turn to right after going through the doors.
comment:
I haven't had any issues with this diner, and I eat/use the restrooms here somewhat-often.

I'm not sure if they require you to be a paying customer, but it's definitely worth the dine-in, even for a small dish.

It's a great and quiet place.

Or you could always ask if you have to dine in.

name: Maryvale Baseball Park
directions: Near Section 105 - Family restroom single bathroom

name: Iowa Western Community College
directions: Second floor of Student Center building, right next to tutoring lab in the same hallway, which is diagonally across from the library and bookstore.
comment: Single person unisex accessible restroom with 1 toilet and 1 sink.  Must be a student, employee, or official campus visitor.

name: Liquid Planet
directions: Back of the building, there are two gender neutral single stalls.
comment: I can't say for sure whether or not you have to be a paying customer. Their sides are like a dollar though, so in the event that they play that card...

name: Andover Newton Theological School
directions: This restroom is located in Sturtevant Hall in the lobby.
comment: The building is locked in the evenings as it is part of a school.

name: dino's pizza
street: corner of madison ave and delaware ave

name: Andover Newton Theological School
directions: First floor of Worcester Hall, at end of hall in the stairwell.
comment: This building is locked in the evenings as it is part of a Theological School.  But in the daytime it is accessible.

name: Schulndt Hall
directions: Enter the main entrance then take the stairs to the 2nd floor. The bathroom will be in an entrance to the right.

name: Schlundt Hall
directions: Men's: Walk through the side entrance then turn left when you reach the water fountains. Bathroom is next to room 32C.

name: Whitten Hall
directions: Enter the front entrance then take the stairs to the 2nd floor. Turn to the right, and the bathroom is next to rooms 201 and 211.

name: Anheuser - Busch
directions: Enter the side entrance then go through the doors makrked "Office of Academic Programs/Classrooms 112-124/Stairway." Walk straight, through doors. then take elevator or stairs to the 3rd floor. Bathroom is right there, next to rooms 318 and 319.

name: Anheuser - Busch
directions: Enter the side entrance, then go through the doors marked "Office of Academic Programs/Classrooms 112-124/ Stairway." Walk straight through doors. Then take elevator or stairs to the 2nd floor. Bathroom is right next to rooms 222 and 223.

name: Anheuser - Busch
directions: Enter the side entrance then go through the doors marked "Office of Academic Programs/Classrooms 112-124/Stairway." Walk straight through doors then take elevator or stairs to the second floor. Bathroom is next to rooms 222 and 223.

name: Geological Sciences
directions: Enter the front entrance then take the stairs to the third floor. The bathrooms is between the janitor's closet and room 314.

name: Geological Sciences
directions: Enter the front entrance, then take the stairs to the second floor. The bathroom is between the janitor's closet (212) and room 211.

name: Black Culture Center
directions: Enter the front entrance then turn left. Enter conference room (room 102). The bathroom is next to the water fountain.

name: Black Culture Center
directions: Enter the front entrance then turn right. Then enter computer lab (Room 122). Bathroom is next to the water fountain.

name: Cornell Hall
directions: Enter Cornell and take the elevator to the 5th floor. Turn right at the elevator then go through the hall of offices. The bathroom is at the end of the hall by the staircase.

name: Clark Hall
directions: Enter Clark Hall and take the elevator to the 7th floor. Turn right off of the elevator, then turn right when you reach room 728. The bathroom is across the hall from 733.

name: Clark Hall
directions: Enter Clark Hall and take the elevator to the 7th floor. Turn left off the elevator, then take a left when you reach room 718. The bathroom is directly across the hall from room 737.

name: Clark Hall
directions: Enter Clark Hall and take the elevator to the 3rd floor. Turn right off the elevator. Bathroom can be reached through room 331 or 332.

name: Clark Hall
directions: Enter Clark Hall and take the elevator to the 3rd floor. Turn left off the elevator, and the bathroom is connected to office room 316. There are signs leading to the bathroom.

name: Professional Building
directions: Enter the main entrance,then take the stairs to the 3rd floor. Take a right, then bathroom is marked "Toilet 321" across from room 330.

name: Professional Building
directions: Enter the main entrance, then take the stairs to the 2nd floor. Take a right, then bathroom is marked "toilet 224" across from room #232.

name: Middlebush
directions: This bathroom is lockable, but as 2 stalls and a urinal. Walk through main doors. Then go up stairs of elevator to the 3rd floor. Walk into the department of Sociology, go to the right and it is next to room 339 (janitor's closet).

name: Agriculture Building
directions: Women's: Enter the entrance facing the student center (closest entrance to Memorial Union). Take a right immediately.

name: Agriculture Building
directions: Men's: Enter the entrance facing the student center (closest entrance to memorial union). Take a right immediately.

name: Tate Hall
directions:
Men's: On the third floor, take a left off the elevator, bathroom is on the left nook.

Women's: On the third floor take a left off the elevator. Then take a left at the 304-314 sign. Bathroom is immediately on the left.

name: Arts & Sciences Building-Allen Auditorium
directions: Enter Arts & Sciences, then enter the doors for Allen Auditorium (110). The restroom is directly to the right.
comment: Men Signage

name: City Centre
directions: Third floor behind Palomino restaurant.
comment: Buy a cake pop or croissant from Starbucks or cookie from Mrs. Fields on the first floor by the elevators and they'll give you the code if you ask. There may be separate codes for the different gender bathrooms, so make sure they give you the right one.

name: public restroom
directions: Rt.15 north to Rt.94 turn left onto Rt.94 follow 1/2 mile make left onto Warbash Rd. on right 1,000 ft. from turn. Very safe and secure nobody around.

name: Cumaica: Artesanos del Cafe
directions: In back
comment: For customers.

name: Center for Sex and Culture
directions: Two in front by desk.
comment: Center has limited hours when events are going on.

name: Target
directions: In the front by customer service. (By the parking lot entrance, not the mall entrance.) It is labeled as a "Family Restroom" and is closer to the women's restroom.

name: JW Marriott
directions:
Two "family friendly" restrooms on second floor, one near the FedX and the other at the rear of the building.

One "family-friendly" restroom on third floor near front of the building.

name: Shpeen Hall
directions: Each floor within Shpeen has gender-neutral bathrooms.

name: St Vincent De Paul Thrift
comment: Ask one of the people working there to help you find the well-hidden bathrooms, and maybe for a key. This store is run by Catholics. The workers mind their own business, they never harass or preach to shoppers.

name: Snohomish Library
comment: There's a single-stall unisex restroom in the children's section. It's supposed to be for families who need a changing room for their babies. There are also gendered bathrooms in the lobby.

name: Chase Brexton Health Care
comment: Chase Brexton is a fabulous LGBTQI health center.

name: Friends on Ponce
directions: Ponce across the street from Greens.  In the back
comment: They have a mens and womens marked... you can't tell they are both used by who needs.   Both are singles.  The place is gay owned and operated so they are very considerate.

name: Storm Crow Tavern
directions: Through the hall on the back right side.
comment: There are two bathrooms but they are both ungendered and marked with the same crow sign.

name: Target
directions: Near the gendered restrooms by customer service in the front corner.
comment: This is a "family" restroom--but obviously it is gender free, as well as accessible
